## Default build is MIT-clean; GPLv2 is opt-in

The pre-built release bundles ArcFormats.dll built in the DEFAULT configuration,
which contains NO GPLv2 code:

  * Blowfish (ArcFormats/Blowfish.cs) has been reimplemented from the public-domain
    Blowfish reference (Schneier / Kocher). It is MIT-licensed with this repository
    and contains no Novell GPL code.
  * The GPLv2 file ArcFormats/KogadoCocotte.cs (morkt's C# port of GPLv2 code by
    juicy.gt) is EXCLUDED from the default build. It is compiled in only when the
    INCLUDE_GPL constant is defined.

Therefore the released ArcFormats.dll is MIT-clean. The GPLv2 source file remains
in this repository for an optional opt-in build. If you rebuild with
INCLUDE_GPL defined (which also re-enables Kogado "Cocotte" compression and the
older ShiinaRio WARC RNG index decompression, which reuse that file's range
coder), the resulting ArcFormats.dll becomes a combined work covered by GPLv2
(full text: licenses/GPL-2.0.txt; the corresponding source is this repository).

All code added by this fork, and the CLI packaging, is MIT (see LICENSE).
Invoking GARbro.Console.exe as a separate process (arm's-length) does not place
the calling program under the GPL, even for an INCLUDE_GPL build.
